* to find prot no which port container is running
sudo docker inspect --format='{{.Config.ExposedPorts}}' proj3-app 
  output : map[8080/tcp:{}]
* to find connection of container with particuler port no 
curl -I http://localhost:80
  output : HTTP/1.1 200 OK

Note : use above commands in newly created ec2 server

we can trubleshoot by accessing newly created ec2 and using docker commands in it 
